snippet.textDisplay:
Here’s the thing: I’m a Drake fan and I don’t think Pusha T went too far. Pusha T had all the personal information fed to him so it made the diss track all the easier to create. He beat Drake at the cover art selection and at just clowning him overall however, Duppy is better than TSOA.

Getting too personal is an unwritten rule in actual battle rap though. Shit usually pops off after someone speaks on something they shouldn’t.

The shock value of Pusha T’s diss would outweigh anything Drake could say cause there isn’t much to say about Pusha T negatively. That’s the same exact reason nobody could seriously beef with Kendrick or Cole. Drake was just an easy target to spill beans about tbh.
